						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="bold">King: Kullōttuṅga Chōḻa III Year 7: 1185 A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>This inscription records the gift of five cows in order to burn a perpetual lamp to the god. Three persons, Tirunāmattūkkāṇi Kaṟpāḍinanda Paguvāyaṉ Vīra Śōḻakōṉ received two cows, Puttuḍaipūraṉ Kōḍaṉ Mūvāyirattuoruvaṉ received a cow and Bhaṭṭan Perukandāṉ received two cows for supplying ghee for the lamp.</p>						

						</summary>
